<TEXT>
a twinengine plane exploded and tumbled 
into a dam in southern india and all 11 people aboard were feared 
dead airline officials said sunday 
officials of the domestic carrier vayudoot said the dornier 
aircraft exploded saturday night about half an hour after takeoff 
from poona airport and fell into the unani dam on the bhima river 
about 90 miles away 
police and investigators ruled out any chances of survivors 
among the eight passengers and three crew members on the hourlong 
flight to hyderabad the names of the victims were not released 
but the airline said all aboard were indian 
rescue teams were searching for bodies and trying to retrieve 
the aircrafts fuselage from 30 feet of water officials said 
aviation investigators were sent to the dam near the village of 
warangal they said they hoped to find out whether the explosion 
was accidental or sabotage 
vayudoot operates short routes mainly in northeastern india 
the airline like indias other two carriers indian airlines and 
air india are operated by the government 
the last major accident involving a vayudoot plane occured on 
oct 19 1988 when a fokker friendship plane slammed into a 
mountain in northeastern india during a torrential rainstorm and 
killed all 34 people on board 
