resolution be a onetime humanitarian action 
the newspaper did not identify its sources and bonn government 
officials declined to comment on the reported plan 
the main difficulty is according to diplomats how it can be 
guaranteed that poland will not become a continually open door as 
is the case with hungary the newspaper reported 
an attorney acting on honeckers behalf met two days ago with 
west german chancellor helmut kohls chief of staff rudolf 
seiters to discuss the developments that have forced bonn to shut 
its embassies in prague and warsaw for now 
more than 700 east germans are packing the mission in prague 
and another 200 are sheltered at the embassy in warsaw awaiting a 
diplomatic solution to their demands to emigrate 
poland has shown reluctance to emulate hungarys bold action in 
letting the east germans go west without permission of their 
government and czechoslovakia has been even slower than east 
germany to loosen travel and emigration restrictions 
the numbers occupying the embassies in prague and warsaw have 
grown by 50 to 100 per day over the past week indicating along 
with the steady flow through hungary continued interest among east 
germans in joining the westward caravan 
east germans need no special permission to travel to 
czechoslovakia and visits to poland are also much easier to 
arrange than trips to the west or permission to emigrate 
