chinese exiles on sunday chose a student protest 
leader and a former government official to lead an international 
movement to end communist rule in china 
on the final day of a threeday inaugural meeting of the 
federation of democracy in china delegates elected former 
government adviser yan jiaqi as chairman and student protest leader 
wuer kaixi as vicechairman 
im very familiar with political science but im not that 
familiar with politics said yan former director of the 
institute of political science a chinese think tank that advised 
the government on political reforms 
still i think my firm belief in a fair and democratic 
political process will be an advantage in this first year he 
said in an interview 
the 47yearold yan is on chinas wanted list accused of 
counterrevolutionary crimes 
he worked closely with the students who occupied beijings 
central tiananmen square for weeks until they were crushed in an 
armed military attack june 34 
chinese authorities say 300 people were killed including dozens 
of security personnel but witnesses and western diplomats say 
hundreds perhaps thousands may have died 
wuer 21 is one of the bestknown of 21 student leaders 
accused of counterrevolutionary crimes in a national tv 
newscast he confronted hardline premier li peng and fainted 
after his speech 
he was smuggled out of china in late june he was a student at 
beijing normal university and is now studying at harvard university 
all of my views arent always those of yan jiaqi but i think 
thats good it is democracy he told delegates everything 
with us must be open everyone must be heard but democracy is not 
the end its the means the means to a brighter future for china 
the new group favors economic sanctions to put pressure on the 
communist authorities and encourage its aims of bringing democracy 
and respect for human rights to china ending oneparty rule and 
developing an open economy that responds to market forces 
jiaqi and wuer won by a vote of 9644 against two challengers 
from california xu sike a doctoral candidate in music at 
stanford university and yang jian li a student at the university 
of california at berkeley 
