the gallows bay crab amp 
oyster house carried an encouraging sign in its window 
open it read todays special food 
a week after hurricane hugo ravaged the island of st croix 
followed by widespread looting dazed residents slowly are getting 
their lives back in order 
relief supplies have arrived power crews have begun work on 
electrical lines and a few businesses have reopened on the 
sidewalk in front of one boardedup photo shop a merchant sold 
boxes of film from a table on saturday 
