<TEXT>
francois michelin whose company agreed friday to 
acquire the ohiobased uniroyal goodrich tire co has proven to be 
as durable the radial tire his company introduced 43 years ago 
for decades michelin has adhered to a style of management 
marked by secrecy thrift and an aversion to outside interference 
such as that by government and unions 
the company believes in technology and invests about 5 percent 
of profits in research and development in 1946 it introduced the 
radial tire and virtually transformed the industry drivers around 
the world now buy radials for their superior handling qualities and 
durablity 
the company remains committed to only two activities making 
tires and producing guidebooks and maps for drivers who ride on 
them 
you will always need a spring between your bottom and the 
road and air will always be the cheapest spring he told the 
financial times in one of his very rare interviews 
the secretive mans company assembles its own production 
machines rather than let another firm see what equipment it is 
using 
it takes our engineers 10 years to put out a new tire or 
develop a new machine michelin 63 has said but five minutes 
is enough to understand the process and thus copy it and put our 
employees out of work 
but the more than 20000 michelin employees who lost their jobs 
in the mid1980s did not have corporate espionage to blame rather 
the company was forced to scale back by a general recession in the 
tire industry 
the downturn could not have come at a worse time for michelin 
one of the few big french enterprises to keep its headquarters in 
the province where it was born 
after capturing the lions share of the european tire market 
the clermontferrandbased company decided in the 1970s to put 
america on radials it built five plants and a large test center 
in the united states from 1978 and 1982 spending more than 3 
billion it also expanded operations into canada and brazil 
the fast expansion followed by the sudden recession was further 
complicated by a rise in interest rates and the dollar michelin 
had borrowed heavily to finance the us growth 
but after several years of struggle michelin watched profits 
soar in the first six months of 1989 to the equivalent of about 
250 million up 281 percent from the first half of 1988 
on friday michelin offered to pay 690 million for uniroyal and 
assume 810 million in debt officials of the akron ohiobased 
company said 
the deal if approved will allow michelin to overtake goodyear 
as the worlds largest tire maker 
tall and slim with a piercing look francois michelin is called 
le patron or the boss by his staff while the company founded 
by his father is called simply la maison or the house 
he is known for being suspicious of luxury he dresses in worn 
suits travels in economy class and when in paris on business 
takes the subway 
trained in mathematics his interests reportedly lean toward the 
metaphysical and his politics to the conservative 
it is michelins opinion that every french government since 1936 
has conducted a socialistic policy by promoting wealth 
redistribution he has said the government has deprived people 
of the responsiblity of their own fate 
